{{About-distinguish|Roger Revelle Prize of the Scripps Institution|Roger Revelle Medal}}
The '''Roger Revelle Prize''' is a prize given out by the [[Scripps Institution of Oceanography]] to people who have made outstanding contributions that advance or promote scientific research in fields such as [[oceanography]], [[climatology]] and other planetary sciences.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://scripps.ucsd.edu/people/awards/revelle|title= Roger Revelle Prize|publisher=Scripps Institution of Oceanography|accessdate = 22 December 2014}} </ref> This prize is named for [[Roger Revelle]], a scientist who served as director of the Scripps Institution of Oceanography and was instrumental in the founding of the [[University of California, San Diego]]. He was an important oceanographer and a pioneer in [[climate change]] research.
The inaugural recipient of this prize was [[Al Gore]], the former [[Vice President of the United States]]. He was awarded the prize on 6 March 2009 for his efforts to bring climate change and environmental issues to a worldwide audience.<ref>[http://www.sdnews.com/pages/full_story?article-Scripps%20to%20salute%20centennial%20of%20UCSD%20founder-oceanographer%20Roger%20Revelle%20=&page_label=home&id=2036055-Scripps+to+salute+centennial+of+UCSD+founder-oceanographer+Roger+Revelle&widget=push&instance=home_news&open=& Scripps to salute centennial of UCSD founder/oceanographer Roger Revelle]</ref> The second recipient of this prize was [[Albert II, Prince of Monaco|Prince Albert of Monaco]]. He was awarded the prize on 23 October 2009 for his efforts to promote scientific research and protection of the environment.<ref>[http://www.cbs8.com/global/story.asp?s=11375865 San Diego gives Monaco's Prince Albert the royal treatment]</ref><ref>[http://scrippsnews.ucsd.edu/Releases/?releaseID=972 Scripps to Honor Prince Albert II of Monaco for his Environmental Efforts]</ref><ref>[http://ucsdnews.ucsd.edu/thisweek/2009/11/02_princealbert.asp A Prize Fit for a Prince]</ref>
