'''Sweet chestnut of Mount Tota''' ({{lang-tr|Tota Dağı Anadolu Kestanesi}}) is an old chestnut tree in [[Isparta Province]], western Turkey.  It is a registered [[List of natural monuments of Turkey|natural monument]] of the country.

The chestnut tree is located on [[Mount Tota]] at [[Kasımlar, Sütçüler|Kasımlar]] village in [[Sütçüler]] district of Isparta Province. It is a sweet chestnut (''[[Castanea sativa]]''). The tree is {{convert|12|m|ft|abbr=on}} high, has a circumference of {{convert|3.10|m|ft|abbr=on}} at {{convert|1|m|ft|abbr=on}} diameter. Its age is dated to be about 190 years old.<ref name="tz"/>

The tree was registered a [[natural monument]] on September 6, 2002. The protected area of the plant covers {{convert|1000|m2|sqft|abbr=on}}.<ref name="tz"/><ref name="mp"/>

